Syntax for Sql (Mircosoft SQL Server ):-

--> Categories for SQL:-
- DDL : Data Definition Language : create, drop, alter, truncate
- DML : Data Manipulation Language : insert, update, delete, select, (merge 
- DQL : Data Query Language : select
- DCL : Data Control Language : grant, revoke, deny)
- TCL : Transactional Control Language : begin transaction, save transaction, commit, rollback


--> Database objects:-
- tables
- views
- indexes
- schemas
- procedures
- functions
- triggers


--> Data Integrity Constraints:-
- NOT NULL
- UNIQUE
- PRIMARY KEY
- FOREIGN KEY
- CHECK
- DEFAULT


--> Categories of datatypes:-
1) String
  - char(n) : A FIXED length string
  - varchar(n) : A VARIABLE length string

2) Numeric
  - int : Used for standard whole numbers (integers)
  - numeric(n) : Used for exact decimal numbers, defining the total number of digits (n).
  - decimal(p,s) : Used for exact decimal numbers, defining total digits (p) and decimal places (s)
  - real : for number with unknown decimal
  - bit [boolean] : 0 (False), 1 (True), or NULL

3) Date & Time
  - date [YYYY-MM-DD] 
  - time [HH:MM:SS] 
  - datetime [YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS]

--> Comments in sql:-
1) -- double hyphen is for a single line comment
2) /* and this
    is a 
    multiline comment*/

--> DDL:-
A. --- CREATE Command ---
1) create database {databasename};
2) use {databasename};
3) create table {tablename} (
    {attribute_name1} {datatype} {contraint [if any]},
    {attribute_name2} {datatype} {contraint [if any]},
    {attribute_name3} {datatype} {contraint [if any]},
    {attribute_name4} {datatype} {contraint [if any]}
    );

B. --- ALTER COMMAND ---
1) add/drop columns
2) add/drop constraints
3) modify columns
4) rename table/columns

c. --- DROP Command ---
1) drop database {databasename};
2) drop table {table_name};

D. --- TRUNCATE Command ---
1) truncate table {table_name};


